==English==

===Etymology===
Derived from Vulgar Latin ''maternalis'', from Classical Latin ''maternus'', from ''mater'' "mother"

===Pronunciation===
*mə-tû(r)'nəl, /mə'tɜː(r)nəl/, /<tt>m@"t3:(r)n@l</tt>/
*:[[Rhymes:English:-ɜː(r)nəl|Rhymes: -ɜː(r)nəl]]

===Adjective===
'''maternal'''

# Pertaining to a mother, her genes, her relatives, or her side of a family.
#: ''maternal grandfather''
# Motherly.
# Received or inherited from someone's mother.
# Of or pertaining to pregnancy.
#: ''maternal death''
# Committed by a mother.
#: ''maternal filicide''

